The bill would essentially favour “in-market surveillance” for goods entering Northern Ireland, Irish journalist Tony Connely reported. He wrote on Twitter: “The centrepiece of the bill is expected to be focused on a ‘dual regulatory regime’ where goods produced in GB would be free to circulate in Northern Ireland, and goods produced in Northern Ireland would be free to circulate in GB.” He stressed, however, its provisions could have “serious implications” for the food and drink industry in NI, particularly for the dairy industry which relies on UK grain for its feedstocks. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...  